<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-331] &#8220;ERROR Failed to write log event to MongoDB due to invalid result [0]&#8221; when using NoSQLAppender</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-331</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I get following message &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    ERROR Failed to write log event to MongoDB due to invalid result &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when using NoSQLAppender with log4j2 v2.0-beta8 but log event gets written to MongoDB.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is my config&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;    &amp;lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;configuration status=&quot;WARN&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;appenders&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;NoSql name=&quot;databaseAppender&quot; suppressExceptions=&quot;true&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;MongoDb collectionName=&quot;applicationLog&quot; factoryClassName=&quot;com.borsch.DBManager&quot; factoryMethodName=&quot;getNewMongoClient&quot; writeConcernConstant=&quot;NONE&quot; username=&quot;root&quot; password=&quot;qwe&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/NoSql&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/appenders&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;loggers&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;root level=&quot;error&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;appender-ref ref=&quot;databaseAppender&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/root&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/loggers&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/configuration&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s even more strange I can&apos;t find the code that generates it. I didn&apos;t find such string in sources of log4j2.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;JDK 1.7, Mongo Driver 2.11.2&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
